    <main>
      <div class="container mt-5">
        <h1 class="faq-header">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <div class="mb-2">
          Here are some of the most common questions we receive about
          SSStutterBuddy:
        </div>
        <!-- Accordion for FAQ -->
        <div class="accordion" id="faqAccordion">
          <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading1">
              <button
                class="accordion-button fw-bold fs-5"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#faqCollapse1"
                aria-expanded="true"
                aria-controls="faqCollapse1"
              >
                How will SSStutterBuddy protect my privacy?
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div
              id="faqCollapse1"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
              aria-labelledby="faqHeading1"
              data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>
                  SSStutterBuddy cares about protecting the privacy of our
                  users. (And unlike most tech companies, we actually mean it!)
                </p>
                <p>
                  The only information SSStutterBuddy requires from you is your
                  first name, last name (or initial), and the town where you
                  reside. We ask for your town of residence in order to connect
                  you with studies being conducted near you.
                </p>
                <p>
                  SSStutterBuddy is a sealed environment. Only vetted
                  researchers are able to view participants on the platform.
                  <strong
                    >There is no way for strangers or even other PWS to see who
                    is on the platform.</strong
                  >
                </p>
                <p>
                  Furthermore, your name will not be displayed to researchers
                  unless you confirm interest in participating in their study.
                  When you show up in a researcher’s search results, it shows a
                  randomly-generated alias like:
                </p>

                <table class="table table-striped">
                  <thead>
                    <tr>
                      <th scope="col">Location</th>
                      <th scope="col">Distance</th>
                      <th scope="col">Invite</th>
                      <th scope="col">Message</th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr>
                      <th>Blue Enhydra lutris</th>
                      <td>2 miles away</td>
                      <td><a href="#">Invite to study</a></td>
                      <td><a href="#">Send message</a></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <th>Ursae Minoris</th>
                      <td>16 miles away</td>
                      <td><a href="#">Invite to study</a></td>
                      <td><a href="#">Send message</a></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <th>Iago Acrostic</th>
                      <td>3192 miles away</td>
                      <td><a href="#">Invite to study</a></td>
                      <td><a href="#">Send message</a></td>
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>

                <p>
                  SSStutterBuddy will have an anonymous email service (like
                  Craigslist) that allows researchers and PWS to send messages
                  back and forth without disclosing the identity of the PWS.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading2">
              <button
                class="accordion-button fw-bold fs-5 collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#faqCollapse2"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="faqCollapse2"
              >
                How can I tell if I want to participate in a study?
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div
              id="faqCollapse2"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="faqHeading2"
              data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>
                  SSStutterBuddy is free and will always be free. SSStutterBuddy
                  will neither charge researchers for posting studies, nor take
                  a cut from the compensation given to study participants.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Our mission is to help advance stuttering research. As such,
                  we feel that any money earmarked for research should go either
                  towards the PWS who participate in studies or the study
                  itself, not a third-party application.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading3">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed fw-bold fs-5"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#faqCollapse3"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="faqCollapse3"
              >
                How does SSStutterBuddy make money?
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div
              id="faqCollapse3"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="faqHeading3"
              data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>That's the neat part. It doesn't.</p>
                <h5 class="fw-bold">
                  But building a web application is expensive. How will
                  SSStutterBuddy do it without money?
                </h5>
                <p>
                  The most expensive part of creating a new web application is
                  not buying the technology, it’s paying the developers who
                  write the code. SSStutterBuddy’s founder, Tom Lovett, is a
                  professional web developer who has donated personal time to
                  build this project.
                </p>
                <p>
                  If you would like to volunteer for the project, send an email
                  to ssstutterbuddy@gmail.com. Technical skills are preferred,
                  but anyone can help!
                </p>
                <p>
                  SSStutterBuddy will accept donations to help defray the minor
                  costs of hosting the website. Large donations will be put
                  towards hiring professional talent to supplement volunteer
                  work.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
